The Washington Post revealed poor treatment of wounded soldiers at Walter Reed, leading to investigations and promises of accountability.
Democratic Senator Barack Obama emphasized the need for top-quality care for veterans.
Defense Secretary Robert Gates appointed a panel to review treatment processes at Walter Reed and the National Naval Medical Center.
Outrage from Congress and veterans groups prompted calls for swift action to address substandard conditions.
Repairs are promised for Building 18, where soldiers face bureaucratic hurdles and neglect.
The Army faces criticism for long-standing issues at Walter Reed, with promises of reform and accountability.
